This paper deals with programming language features such as exceptions, continuations, and higher-order references, which are typically studied in the subfield of programming languages (cs.PL). The paper also discusses the semantics of these features and their relationship, which falls under the subfield of logic in computer science (cs.LO). Additionally, the paper discusses control flow analysis of exception handling, which is a topic in software engineering (cs.SE). The paper also mentions the use of monads, which are a common tool in functional programming, falling under the subfield of formal languages (cs.FL). Finally, the paper discusses the proof of definability, which is a topic in theoretical computer science (cs.TP).
